						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab (No. 5) lying near <hi rend="italic">hōma-kunḍa</hi> in the Pañchaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇadēvarāya, 1523 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1445, Bhādrapada śu. 15,</hi> Tuesday. The cyclic year is lost. But in the given Śaka year the details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1523 A.D., August 25, Tuesday, f.d.t. ·06.</hi> The cyclic year was Subhānu.</p>						

						<p>It refers to <hi rend="bold">Viṭharasa-voḍeya,</hi> son of <hi rend="italic">karaṇika</hi> <hi rend="bold">Lakshmīnārāya[ṇavoḍeya*]</hi> as governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
